{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784180499486,"sessionID":"ses_0968f2113ffehJfWsGHuGr12Oc","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_7675c8c84d8047c39695e4fa","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Strategy Template\n3: description: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep research strategy\"\n6:   - \"research strategy template\"\n7:   - \"research session tracking\"\n8:   - \"exhausted research approaches\"\n9:   - \"research stop conditions\"\n10:   - \"ruled out research directions\"\n11: importance_tier: normal\n12: contextType: planning\n13: version: 1.14.0.19\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n17: \n18: Runtime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\n19: \n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n21: \n22: ### Purpose\n23: \n24: Serves as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep research session. Records what to investigate, what worked, what failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n25: \n26: ### Usage\n27: \n28: - **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{spec_folder}/research/deep-research-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Key Questions, Known Context, and Research Boundaries from config and memory context.\n29: - **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, writes iteration evidence, and the reducer refreshes What Worked/Failed, answered questions, carried-forward questions, ruled-out directions, and Next Focus.\n30: - **Mutability:** Mutable — analyst-owned sections remain stable, while machine-owned sections are rewritten by the reducer after each iteration. Section 3 is a generated projection from the reducer registry.\n31: - **Protection:** Shared state with explicit ownership boundaries. Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n32: \n33: ### Question Injection Surface\n34: \n35: Use `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl` to append external questions during an active run. Each line is one JSON object with:\n36: \n37: - `id`: stable inbox record identifier\n38: - `text`: question text to promote\n39: - `source`: concrete source label, such as an angle bank entry, analyst strategy, or operator note\n40: - `origin`: one of `angle-bank`, `analyst-strategy`, `operator`, or `legacy-import`\n41: - `injectedAtIteration`: iteration number when the question was introduced\n42: - `promotedQuestionId`: promoted registry question id, or `null` until promotion\n43: \n44: The reducer reads the inbox on every reduce step and carries `origin` into the question registry and dashboard badges. Direct edits to Section 3 still work as a compatibility path, but they are attributed as `legacy-import`.\n45: \n46: Question ownership is explicit:\n47: \n48: - Inbox rows are immutable input.\n49: - The reducer registry is canonical question state.\n50: - Section 3 is rendered only from the registry view.\n51: \n52: When an inbox row targets an existing registry question but carries different text, the reducer keeps the registry value, records `operatorDecision: needs_decision`, and appends a `question_conflict` event with both `inboxValue` and `registryValue`.\n53: \n54: ---\n55: \n56: ## 2. TOPIC\n57: [Research topic from config -- set during initialization]\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n62: ## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n63: Generated from the reducer registry. Add external or late questions through `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl`; direct edits are imported as compatibility input and may be replaced on the next reduce step.\n64: \n65: - [ ] [Question 1 -- identified during initialization or iteration 1]\n66: - [ ] [Question 2]\n67: - [ ] [Question 3]\n68: <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: ## 4. NON-GOALS\n73: [What this research session is NOT trying to answer -- populated during initialization]\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n78: [Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n83: ## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n84: [None yet -- populated as iterations answer questions]\n85: <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n86: \n87: ---\n88: \n89: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n90: <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n91: ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n92: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n93: - [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n94: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n95: \n96: ---\n97: \n98: <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n99: ## 8. WHAT FAILED\n100: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n101: - [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n102: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n103: \n104: ---\n105: \n106: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n107: ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n108: [Populated when an approach has been tried from multiple angles without success]\n109: \n110: ### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n111: - What was tried: [specific approaches attempted]\n112: - Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n113: - Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n114: \n115: ### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n116: - What worked: [successful approaches in this category]\n117: - Prefer for: [related questions where this category may help]\n118: <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n119: \n120: ---\n121: \n122: <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n123: ## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n124: [Approaches that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n125: - [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n126: <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n127: \n128: ---\n129: \n130: <!-- ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n131: ## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n132: - Completed pivots: 0\n133: - Failed pivots: 0\n134: - Audited overrides: 0\n135: - Saturated: none yet\n136: - Pivot lineage: none yet\n137: - Remaining frontier: none recorded\n138: <!-- /ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n139: \n140: ---\n141: \n142: <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n143: ## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n144: [Self-owned open questions from iteration write-back -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n145: <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n146: \n147: ---\n148: \n149: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n150: ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n151: [Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration]\n152: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n153: \n154: ---\n155: \n156: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n157: ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n158: [Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n159: \n160: ### Bounded Context Snapshot\n161: \n162: Populate during initialization when the target is codebase-scoped. Keep this pointer-based and small:\n163: \n164: - Source pointers: paths, symbols, or resource-map entries relevant to the topic.\n165: - Reuse candidates: existing utilities, patterns, docs, or agents worth extending.\n166: - Integration points: files or contracts the research is likely to touch.\n167: - Constraints and risks: scope limits, stale graph or memory gaps, and known non-goals.\n168: \n169: Do not inline full source bodies. Do not dispatch the retired standalone context loop. Use `@context` for one-shot retrieval, and use this snapshot only to seed the research loop.\n170: \n171: ---\n172: \n173: ## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n174: - Max iterations: [from config]\n175: - Convergence threshold: [from config]\n176: - Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n177: - Progressive synthesis: true (default)\n178: - research/research.md ownership: workflow-owned canonical synthesis output\n179: - Lifecycle branches: `resume`, `restart` (live); `fork`, `completed-continue` (deferred, not runtime-wired)\n180: - Machine-owned sections: reducer controls Sections 3, 6, 7-11A, including Section 10A pivot lineage\n181: - Question injection surface: `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl`\n182: - Question conflict owner: reducer registry; `question_conflict` events surface inbox/registry disagreements for operator decision\n183: - Canonical pause sentinel: `research/.deep-research-pause`\n184: - Capability matrix: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json`\n185: - Capability matrix doc: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md`\n186: - Capability resolver: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs`\n187: - Current generation: [from config.lineage.generation]\n188: - Started: [timestamp]\n\n(End of file - total 188 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep research strategy\"\n  - \"research strategy template\"\n  - \"research session tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted research approaches\"\n  - \"research stop conditions\"\n  - \"ruled out research directions\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\nversion: 1.14.0.19\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep research strategy\"\n  - \"research strategy template\"\n  - \"research session tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted research approaches\"\n  - \"research stop conditions\"\n  - \"ruled out research directions\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\nversion: 1.14.0.19\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nServes as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep research session. Records what to investigate, what worked, what failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n\n### Usage\n\n- **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{spec_folder}/research/deep-research-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Key Questions, Known Context, and Research Boundaries from config and memory context.\n- **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, writes iteration evidence, and the reducer refreshes What Worked/Failed, answered questions, carried-forward questions, ruled-out directions, and Next Focus.\n- **Mutability:** Mutable — analyst-owned sections remain stable, while machine-owned sections are rewritten by the reducer after each iteration. Section 3 is a generated projection from the reducer registry.\n- **Protection:** Shared state with explicit ownership boundaries. Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n\n### Question Injection Surface\n\nUse `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl` to append external questions during an active run. Each line is one JSON object with:\n\n- `id`: stable inbox record identifier\n- `text`: question text to promote\n- `source`: concrete source label, such as an angle bank entry, analyst strategy, or operator note\n- `origin`: one of `angle-bank`, `analyst-strategy`, `operator`, or `legacy-import`\n- `injectedAtIteration`: iteration number when the question was introduced\n- `promotedQuestionId`: promoted registry question id, or `null` until promotion\n\nThe reducer reads the inbox on every reduce step and carries `origin` into the question registry and dashboard badges. Direct edits to Section 3 still work as a compatibility path, but they are attributed as `legacy-import`.\n\nQuestion ownership is explicit:\n\n- Inbox rows are immutable input.\n- The reducer registry is canonical question state.\n- Section 3 is rendered only from the registry view.\n\nWhen an inbox row targets an existing registry question but carries different text, the reducer keeps the registry value, records `operatorDecision: needs_decision`, and appends a `question_conflict` event with both `inboxValue` and `registryValue`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n[Research topic from config -- set during initialization]\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\nGenerated from the reducer registry. Add external or late questions through `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl`; direct edits are imported as compatibility input and may be replaced on the next reduce step.\n\n- [ ] [Question 1 -- identified during initialization or iteration 1]\n- [ ] [Question 2]\n- [ ] [Question 3]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n---\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n[What this research session is NOT trying to answer -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n[Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n[None yet -- populated as iterations answer questions]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n## 7. WHAT WORKED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n## 8. WHAT FAILED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n[Populated when an approach has been tried from multiple angles without success]\n\n### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n- What was tried: [specific approaches attempted]\n- Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n- Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n\n### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n- What worked: [successful approaches in this category]\n- Prefer for: [related questions where this category may help]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n[Approaches that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n- [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n## 10A. SATURATED DIRECTIONS AND DIVERGENCE FRONTIER\n- Completed pivots: 0\n- Failed pivots: 0\n- Audited overrides: 0\n- Saturated: none yet\n- Pivot lineage: none yet\n- Remaining frontier: none recorded\n<!-- /ANCHOR:divergence-frontier -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n[Self-owned open questions from iteration write-back -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n[Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n[Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n\n### Bounded Context Snapshot\n\nPopulate during initialization when the target is codebase-scoped. Keep this pointer-based and small:\n\n- Source pointers: paths, symbols, or resource-map entries relevant to the topic.\n- Reuse candidates: existing utilities, patterns, docs, or agents worth extending.\n- Integration points: files or contracts the research is likely to touch.\n- Constraints and risks: scope limits, stale graph or memory gaps, and known non-goals.\n\nDo not inline full source bodies. Do not dispatch the retired standalone context loop. Use `@context` for one-shot retrieval, and use this snapshot only to seed the research loop.\n\n---\n\n## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n- Max iterations: [from config]\n- Convergence threshold: [from config]\n- Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n- Progressive synthesis: true (default)\n- research/research.md ownership: workflow-owned canonical synthesis output\n- Lifecycle branches: `resume`, `restart` (live); `fork`, `completed-continue` (deferred, not runtime-wired)\n- Machine-owned sections: reducer controls Sections 3, 6, 7-11A, including Section 10A pivot lineage\n- Question injection surface: `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl`\n- Question conflict owner: reducer registry; `question_conflict` events surface inbox/registry disagreements for operator decision\n- Canonical pause sentinel: `research/.deep-research-pause`\n- Capability matrix: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json`\n- Capability matrix doc: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md`\n- Capability resolver: `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs`\n- Current generation: [from config.lineage.generation]\n- Started: [timestamp]","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":188,"totalLines":188,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md","time":{"start":1784180499454,"end":1784180499478}},"id":"prt_f6971e3fd001dKiUQclJJVzdsC","sessionID":"ses_0968f2113ffehJfWsGHuGr12Oc","messageID":"msg_f6971b2cd001Y0dD5GjRvjnLKT"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784180499486,"sessionID":"ses_0968f2113ffehJfWsGHuGr12Oc","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_471f34de61574d109ef6fdd2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Convergence Detection Reference\n3: description: Live stop contract and navigation hub for deep-research convergence.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research convergence detection\"\n6:   - \"research stop contract\"\n7:   - \"research stopreason values\"\n8:   - \"research legal stop gates\"\n9:   - \"research convergence decision order\"\n10: importance_tier: important\n11: contextType: implementation\n12: version: 1.14.0.21\n13: ---\n14: \n15: # Convergence Detection Reference\n16: \n17: Live stop-contract hub for deep-research convergence and routed convergence references.\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n22: \n23: ### Purpose\n24: \n25: Keep the executable deep-research stop contract short enough to load during routing while pointing detailed signal, recovery, and graph behavior to focused references.\n26: \n27: ### When to Use\n28: \n29: Load this hub when deciding whether a deep-research loop should continue, recover, or stop.\n30: \n31: ### Key Sources\n32: \n33: - Command syntax: `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md`\n34: - Workflow algorithm: `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml` and `_confirm.yaml`\n35: - Signal details: `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`\n36: - Recovery details: `references/convergence/convergence_recovery.md`\n37: - Graph stop gates: `references/convergence/convergence_graph.md`\n38: \n39: For iterative code review convergence, use `deep-review`. Review-mode algorithms and state are not part of the deep-research live contract.\n40: \n41: ### Live Decision Model\n42: \n43: Convergence decides whether the loop should continue, recover from a stuck state, or stop. A STOP candidate is not legal until the legal-stop gate bundle passes. Novelty math can nominate STOP; gates authorize it.\n44: \n45: The live deep-research algorithm evaluates:\n46: \n47: | Stage | Outcome |\n48: |-------|---------|\n49: | Hard stop and completion candidate | Stop unconditionally on max iterations; nominate STOP when all key questions are answered |\n50: | Stuck detection | Enter recovery after configured consecutive no-progress iterations |\n51: | Composite convergence | Nominate STOP when weighted signal score is above `0.60` |\n52: | Legal-stop gates | Allow or block the STOP candidate |\n53: | Graph gates | Add STOP-blocking graph checks when `graphEvents` exist |\n54: \n55: ### Convergence Modes\n56: \n57: The shared convergence runtime accepts four values. The workflow keeps hard terminal boundaries outside mode-specific convergence handling.\n58: \n59: | Mode | Live Behavior |\n60: |------|---------------|\n61: | `default` | Uses the normal full-history convergence signals and sends a legal STOP to synthesis. This is the fallback when no mode is supplied. |\n62: | `off` | Skips convergence-driven STOP candidates. Max iterations, pause or cancellation, manual stop, recovery halt, and unrecoverable error behavior remain active. |\n63: | `sliding-window` | Uses a bounded graph-novelty window, defaulting to 5 snapshots, while preserving the ordinary legal-stop and synthesis path. |\n64: | `divergent` | Computes convergence normally, but translates an eligible legal STOP into a three-seat direction-selection pivot and continues from the selected focus. |\n65: \n66: #### Divergent Pivot Contract\n67: \n68: Research pivots are eligible only when the workflow decision is `STOP` and the exact internal reason is `composite_converged` or `all_questions_answered`. The legal-stop and quality gates run before this branch. `maxIterationsReached`, `blockedStop`, `stuckRecovery`, `minIterationsNotReached`, `error`, `manualStop`, and `userPaused` are explicitly excluded. Max iterations, pause or cancellation, manual stop, and unrecoverable error therefore never dispatch a pivot Council.\n69: \n70: Each eligible pivot runs one native, in-process Council round with exactly three distinct seats: analytical, critical, and pragmatic. It does not use an external CLI. The transaction requires all three seat returns to be parse-valid and at least two seats to materially endorse the same candidate without a high-severity blocker. Research candidates come from persisted adjacent questions, contradiction or verification gaps, missing source classes, alternate evidence methods, and independent checks of recent findings. A completed pivot restores the selected candidate's focus and returns to the research loop; a failed pivot fails closed to synthesis.\n71: \n72: Every pivot dispatches three seats, so a run that pivots has proportionally higher model cost and duration than the same run under `default`, `off`, or `sliding-window`. Pivot evidence is isolated under `<artifactRoot>/divergent/pivots/<pivotId>/council/**`, including config, append-only state, three seat artifacts, deliberation, and report. This path is distinct from ordinary planning Council artifacts under a spec packet's `ai-council/**` tree.\n73: \n74: ---\n75: \n76: ## 2. STOP CONTRACT\n77: \n78: ### stopReason Values\n79: \n80: | Value | When It Is Used |\n81: |-------|-----------------|\n82: | `converged` | Legal-stop gates passed and the loop may exit normally |\n83: | `maxIterationsReached` | The loop hit the configured iteration cap |\n84: | `userPaused` | A pause sentinel or equivalent user pause request halted execution |\n85: | `blockedStop` | A STOP candidate was blocked by legal-stop or graph gates |\n86: | `stuckRecovery` | Stuck detection triggered or failed recovery |\n87: | `error` | The loop hit an unrecoverable workflow or state error |\n88: \n89: ### Legacy Stop Labels\n90: \n91: Legacy labels are normalized before persistence:\n92: \n93: | Legacy label or phrase | New `stopReason` |\n94: |------------------------|------------------|\n95: | `composite_converged` | `converged` |\n96: | `novelty below threshold` | `converged` |\n97: | `all_questions_answered` | `converged` |\n98: | `max_iterations_reached` | `maxIterationsReached` |\n99: | `paused` | `userPaused` |\n100: | `stuck_detected` | `stuckRecovery` |\n101: | `stuck_unrecoverable` | `stuckRecovery` |\n102: \n103: ---\n104: \n105: ## 3. LIVE ALGORITHM\n106: \n107: ### Decision Order\n108: \n109: ```text\n110: 1. If iteration count >= maxIterations, STOP with maxIterationsReached.\n111: 2. If all key questions have evidence-backed answers, nominate STOP.\n112: 3. If stuckCount >= stuckThreshold, enter stuck recovery.\n113: 4. Compute composite convergence signals.\n114: 5. If weighted stop score > 0.60, nominate STOP.\n115: 6. Evaluate legal-stop gates for every STOP candidate except hard max-iteration stop.\n116: 7. If graphEvents exist, evaluate graph-aware STOP blockers.\n117: 8. If gates pass, pivot for an eligible divergent reason or STOP normally; otherwise emit blockedStop and CONTINUE with recovery focus.\n118: ```\n119: \n120: ### Composite Signal Weights\n121: \n122: | Signal | Weight | Min Iterations | Measures |\n123: |--------|--------|----------------|----------|\n124: | Rolling Average | `0.30` | 3 evidence iterations | Recent information yield |\n125: | MAD Noise Floor | `0.35` | 4 evidence iterations | Signal vs noise in `newInfoRatio` |\n126: | Question Entropy | `0.35` | 1 key question | Evidence-backed question coverage |\n127: \n128: The weighted stop score is normalized over active signals. STOP is nominated only when the normalized score is greater than `0.60`. See `convergence_signals.md` for exact signal rules and reporting.\n129: \n130: ---\n131: \n132: ## 4. LEGAL STOP GATES\n133: \n134: Every non-terminal STOP candidate must pass the gate bundle before the workflow exits.\n135: \n136: | Gate | Rule | Failure |\n137: |------|------|---------|\n138: | Convergence Gate | Low novelty holds for the required consecutive evidence iterations | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n139: | Coverage Gate | Every key question has an evidence-backed answer | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n140: | Quality Gate | Source diversity, focus alignment, and no single weak-source dominance pass | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n141: | Graph Gate | When graph data exists, graph coverage has no STOP blockers | Emit `graph_convergence`/`blocked_stop`, continue |\n142: \n143: The reducer surfaces legal-stop evidence through the findings registry and dashboard. The JSONL event shapes live in `../state/state_jsonl.md`.\n144: \n145: ---\n146: \n147: ## 5. ROUTED REFERENCES\n148: \n149: | Resource | Use When |\n150: |----------|----------|\n151: | `convergence_signals.md` | Need scoring, `newInfoRatio`, `stuckCount`, MAD, entropy, report fields, or threshold tuning |\n152: | `convergence_recovery.md` | Need stuck recovery, recovery strategy selection, tiered errors, or escalation behavior |\n153: | `convergence_graph.md` | Need graph-aware STOP gates, graph convergence events, or coverage graph fallback behavior |\n154: | `convergence_reference_only.md` | Need future/reference-only models such as segment filtering, semantic convergence, or optimizer metadata |\n155: | `../state/state_jsonl.md` | Need JSONL event shapes persisted by the convergence workflow |\n156: | `../state/state_reducer_registry.md` | Need reducer-owned registry/dashboard fields derived from convergence |\n157: \n158: ---\n159: \n160: ## 6. NON-GOALS\n161: \n162: - Do not copy `deep-review` convergence into this skill. Use the `deep-review` references for severity-weighted review convergence.\n163: - Do not treat reference-only semantic or segment models as executable contracts.\n164: - Do not change the YAML workflow by editing this document. This document describes and routes the live contract; workflow changes require command/YAML work.\n\n(End of file - total 164 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Convergence Detection Reference\ndescription: Live stop contract and navigation hub for deep-research convergence.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research convergence detection\"\n  - \"research stop contract\"\n  - \"research stopreason values\"\n  - \"research legal stop gates\"\n  - \"research convergence decision order\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.21\n---\n\n# Convergence Detection Reference\n\nLive stop-contract hub for deep-research convergence and routed convergence references.\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md","text":"---\ntitle: Convergence Detection Reference\ndescription: Live stop contract and navigation hub for deep-research convergence.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research convergence detection\"\n  - \"research stop contract\"\n  - \"research stopreason values\"\n  - \"research legal stop gates\"\n  - \"research convergence decision order\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.21\n---\n\n# Convergence Detection Reference\n\nLive stop-contract hub for deep-research convergence and routed convergence references.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nKeep the executable deep-research stop contract short enough to load during routing while pointing detailed signal, recovery, and graph behavior to focused references.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this hub when deciding whether a deep-research loop should continue, recover, or stop.\n\n### Key Sources\n\n- Command syntax: `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md`\n- Workflow algorithm: `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml` and `_confirm.yaml`\n- Signal details: `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`\n- Recovery details: `references/convergence/convergence_recovery.md`\n- Graph stop gates: `references/convergence/convergence_graph.md`\n\nFor iterative code review convergence, use `deep-review`. Review-mode algorithms and state are not part of the deep-research live contract.\n\n### Live Decision Model\n\nConvergence decides whether the loop should continue, recover from a stuck state, or stop. A STOP candidate is not legal until the legal-stop gate bundle passes. Novelty math can nominate STOP; gates authorize it.\n\nThe live deep-research algorithm evaluates:\n\n| Stage | Outcome |\n|-------|---------|\n| Hard stop and completion candidate | Stop unconditionally on max iterations; nominate STOP when all key questions are answered |\n| Stuck detection | Enter recovery after configured consecutive no-progress iterations |\n| Composite convergence | Nominate STOP when weighted signal score is above `0.60` |\n| Legal-stop gates | Allow or block the STOP candidate |\n| Graph gates | Add STOP-blocking graph checks when `graphEvents` exist |\n\n### Convergence Modes\n\nThe shared convergence runtime accepts four values. The workflow keeps hard terminal boundaries outside mode-specific convergence handling.\n\n| Mode | Live Behavior |\n|------|---------------|\n| `default` | Uses the normal full-history convergence signals and sends a legal STOP to synthesis. This is the fallback when no mode is supplied. |\n| `off` | Skips convergence-driven STOP candidates. Max iterations, pause or cancellation, manual stop, recovery halt, and unrecoverable error behavior remain active. |\n| `sliding-window` | Uses a bounded graph-novelty window, defaulting to 5 snapshots, while preserving the ordinary legal-stop and synthesis path. |\n| `divergent` | Computes convergence normally, but translates an eligible legal STOP into a three-seat direction-selection pivot and continues from the selected focus. |\n\n#### Divergent Pivot Contract\n\nResearch pivots are eligible only when the workflow decision is `STOP` and the exact internal reason is `composite_converged` or `all_questions_answered`. The legal-stop and quality gates run before this branch. `maxIterationsReached`, `blockedStop`, `stuckRecovery`, `minIterationsNotReached`, `error`, `manualStop`, and `userPaused` are explicitly excluded. Max iterations, pause or cancellation, manual stop, and unrecoverable error therefore never dispatch a pivot Council.\n\nEach eligible pivot runs one native, in-process Council round with exactly three distinct seats: analytical, critical, and pragmatic. It does not use an external CLI. The transaction requires all three seat returns to be parse-valid and at least two seats to materially endorse the same candidate without a high-severity blocker. Research candidates come from persisted adjacent questions, contradiction or verification gaps, missing source classes, alternate evidence methods, and independent checks of recent findings. A completed pivot restores the selected candidate's focus and returns to the research loop; a failed pivot fails closed to synthesis.\n\nEvery pivot dispatches three seats, so a run that pivots has proportionally higher model cost and duration than the same run under `default`, `off`, or `sliding-window`. Pivot evidence is isolated under `<artifactRoot>/divergent/pivots/<pivotId>/council/**`, including config, append-only state, three seat artifacts, deliberation, and report. This path is distinct from ordinary planning Council artifacts under a spec packet's `ai-council/**` tree.\n\n---\n\n## 2. STOP CONTRACT\n\n### stopReason Values\n\n| Value | When It Is Used |\n|-------|-----------------|\n| `converged` | Legal-stop gates passed and the loop may exit normally |\n| `maxIterationsReached` | The loop hit the configured iteration cap |\n| `userPaused` | A pause sentinel or equivalent user pause request halted execution |\n| `blockedStop` | A STOP candidate was blocked by legal-stop or graph gates |\n| `stuckRecovery` | Stuck detection triggered or failed recovery |\n| `error` | The loop hit an unrecoverable workflow or state error |\n\n### Legacy Stop Labels\n\nLegacy labels are normalized before persistence:\n\n| Legacy label or phrase | New `stopReason` |\n|------------------------|------------------|\n| `composite_converged` | `converged` |\n| `novelty below threshold` | `converged` |\n| `all_questions_answered` | `converged` |\n| `max_iterations_reached` | `maxIterationsReached` |\n| `paused` | `userPaused` |\n| `stuck_detected` | `stuckRecovery` |\n| `stuck_unrecoverable` | `stuckRecovery` |\n\n---\n\n## 3. LIVE ALGORITHM\n\n### Decision Order\n\n```text\n1. If iteration count >= maxIterations, STOP with maxIterationsReached.\n2. If all key questions have evidence-backed answers, nominate STOP.\n3. If stuckCount >= stuckThreshold, enter stuck recovery.\n4. Compute composite convergence signals.\n5. If weighted stop score > 0.60, nominate STOP.\n6. Evaluate legal-stop gates for every STOP candidate except hard max-iteration stop.\n7. If graphEvents exist, evaluate graph-aware STOP blockers.\n8. If gates pass, pivot for an eligible divergent reason or STOP normally; otherwise emit blockedStop and CONTINUE with recovery focus.\n```\n\n### Composite Signal Weights\n\n| Signal | Weight | Min Iterations | Measures |\n|--------|--------|----------------|----------|\n| Rolling Average | `0.30` | 3 evidence iterations | Recent information yield |\n| MAD Noise Floor | `0.35` | 4 evidence iterations | Signal vs noise in `newInfoRatio` |\n| Question Entropy | `0.35` | 1 key question | Evidence-backed question coverage |\n\nThe weighted stop score is normalized over active signals. STOP is nominated only when the normalized score is greater than `0.60`. See `convergence_signals.md` for exact signal rules and reporting.\n\n---\n\n## 4. LEGAL STOP GATES\n\nEvery non-terminal STOP candidate must pass the gate bundle before the workflow exits.\n\n| Gate | Rule | Failure |\n|------|------|---------|\n| Convergence Gate | Low novelty holds for the required consecutive evidence iterations | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n| Coverage Gate | Every key question has an evidence-backed answer | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n| Quality Gate | Source diversity, focus alignment, and no single weak-source dominance pass | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n| Graph Gate | When graph data exists, graph coverage has no STOP blockers | Emit `graph_convergence`/`blocked_stop`, continue |\n\nThe reducer surfaces legal-stop evidence through the findings registry and dashboard. The JSONL event shapes live in `../state/state_jsonl.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. ROUTED REFERENCES\n\n| Resource | Use When |\n|----------|----------|\n| `convergence_signals.md` | Need scoring, `newInfoRatio`, `stuckCount`, MAD, entropy, report fields, or threshold tuning |\n| `convergence_recovery.md` | Need stuck recovery, recovery strategy selection, tiered errors, or escalation behavior |\n| `convergence_graph.md` | Need graph-aware STOP gates, graph convergence events, or coverage graph fallback behavior |\n| `convergence_reference_only.md` | Need future/reference-only models such as segment filtering, semantic convergence, or optimizer metadata |\n| `../state/state_jsonl.md` | Need JSONL event shapes persisted by the convergence workflow |\n| `../state/state_reducer_registry.md` | Need reducer-owned registry/dashboard fields derived from convergence |\n\n---\n\n## 6. NON-GOALS\n\n- Do not copy `deep-review` convergence into this skill. Use the `deep-review` references for severity-weighted review convergence.\n- Do not treat reference-only semantic or segment models as executable contracts.\n- Do not change the YAML workflow by editing this document. This document describes and routes the live contract; workflow changes require command/YAML work.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":164,"totalLines":164,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md","time":{"start":1784180499452,"end":1784180499484}},"id":"prt_f6971e3fa001zZnlR59dHerJkZ","sessionID":"ses_0968f2113ffehJfWsGHuGr12Oc","messageID":"msg_f6971b2cd001Y0dD5GjRvjnLKT"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784180499502,"sessionID":"ses_0968f2113ffehJfWsGHuGr12Oc","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_9cf6f6a4ad654d9c800749e0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"ls -la /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/ 2>/dev/null; echo \"---LINEAGE DIR---\"; ls -la /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/ 2>/dev/null; echo \"---EXIT---\""},"output":"total 32\ndrwxr-xr-x@  6 michelkerkmeester  staff   192 Jul 16 07:38 .\ndrwxr-xr-x@ 18 michelkerkmeester  staff   576 Jul 16 07:37 ..\n-rw-r--r--@  1 michelkerkmeester  staff   772 Jul 16 07:38 description.json\n-rw-r--r--@  1 michelkerkmeester  staff  4089 Jul 16 07:38 graph-metadata.json\ndrwxr-xr-x@  5 michelkerkmeester  staff   160 Jul 16 07:40 research\n-rw-r--r--@  1 michelkerkmeester  staff  6614 Jul 16 07:38 spec.md\n---LINEAGE DIR---\ntotal 0\ndrwxr-xr-x@ 3 michelkerkmeester  staff   96 Jul 16 07:40 .\ndrwxr-xr-x@ 4 michelkerkmeester  staff  128 Jul 16 07:40 ..\ndrwxr-xr-x@ 2 michelkerkmeester  staff   64 Jul 16 07:40 .executor-state\n---EXIT---\n","metadata":{"output":"total 32\ndrwxr-xr-x@  6 michelkerkmeester  staff   192 Jul 16 07:38 .\ndrwxr-xr-x@ 18 michelkerkmeester  staff   576 Jul 16 07:37 ..\n-rw-r--r--@  1 michelkerkmeester  staff   772 Jul 16 07:38 description.json\n-rw-r--r--@  1 michelkerkmeester  staff  4089 Jul 16 07:38 graph-metadata.json\ndrwxr-xr-x@  5 michelkerkmeester  staff   160 Jul 16 07:40 research\n-rw-r--r--@  1 michelkerkmeester  staff  6614 Jul 16 07:38 spec.md\n---LINEAGE DIR---\ntotal 0\ndrwxr-xr-x@ 3 michelkerkmeester  staff   96 Jul 16 07:40 .\ndrwxr-xr-x@ 4 michelkerkmeester  staff  128 Jul 16 07:40 ..\ndrwxr-xr-x@ 2 michelkerkmeester  staff   64 Jul 16 07:40 .executor-state\n---EXIT---\n","exit":0,"truncated":false},"title":"ls -la /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/ 2>/dev/null; echo \"---LINEAGE DIR---\"; ls -la /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/ 2>/dev/null; echo \"---EXIT---\"","time":{"start":1784180499499,"end":1784180499501}},"id":"prt_f6971e408001irxTQ2A7Hr8QqM","sessionID":"ses_0968f2113ffehJfWsGHuGr12Oc","messageID":"msg_f6971b2cd001Y0dD5GjRvjnLKT"}}
