{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784181113583,"sessionID":"ses_0968f2113ffehJfWsGHuGr12Oc","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"call_e34a45b0c180439fa261f6ab","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md","newString":"<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n**Iteration 2 — RQ2 per-family conformance recurrence.** Sweep create/design/speckit/memory/doctor/deep to test whether the F1.1–F1.6 defect classes recur across families (→ canon gap, wholesale fix) or are isolated (→ one-off authoring error, per-file fix). Measure: missing-mandatory-gate prevalence, bare MCP tools, argument-hint length distribution, route-manifest topology presence, $ARGUMENTS echo usage. Output: a recurrence matrix mapping each defect class to the families it touches, with a wholesale-vs-per-file verdict per class.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->","oldString":"<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n**Iteration 1 — RQ1 canon completeness.** Read the create-command canon triad (SKILL.md Steps 5–11, `command_router_template.md`, `command_template.md` §11 router split) against the validator's command rules (`template_rules.json` `command` block) and the 066 contract (000 child). Map every canon claim that the validator does NOT enforce, and every validator rule the canon does NOT state, then identify gaps that admit non-conformant commands. Produce file:line evidence + candidate delta per gap.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md\n===========================================