{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784181166914,"sessionID":"ses_0968f2113ffehJfWsGHuGr12Oc","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_cf667bf0428a4aceb5101734","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"cd /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public\necho \"=== deep/research.md head (compiled stub?) ===\"\nhead -20 .opencode/commands/deep/research.md\necho \"\"\necho \"=== router-core markers: clean per-family count ===\"\nfor fam in create design speckit memory doctor deep; do\n  files=$(find .opencode/commands/$f -maxdepth 1 -name '*.md' 2>/dev/null)\n  total=$(echo \"$files\" | grep -c . )\n  core=$(echo \"$files\" | xargs rg -l '## .*OWNED ASSETS' 2>/dev/null | grep -c . )\n  pb=$(echo \"$files\" | xargs rg -l '## .*PRESENTATION BOUNDARY' 2>/dev/null | grep -c . )\n  echo \"$f: total=$total owned_assets=$core presentation_boundary=$pb\"\ndone\necho \"\"\necho \"=== commands with NEITHER owned-assets NOR purpose/instructions (potential non-conformant) ===\"\nfor f in $(find .opencode/commands -maxdepth 2 -name '*.md'); do\n  has_ow=$(rg -c 'OWNED ASSETS' \"$f\" 2>/dev/null || echo 0)\n  has_pur=$(rg -c '^## .*PURPOSE' \"$f\" 2>/dev/null || echo 0)\n  has_ins=$(rg -c '^## .*INSTRUCTIONS' \"$f\" 2>/dev/null || echo 0)\n  if [ \"$has_ow\" = \"0\" ] && [ \"$has_pur\" = \"0\" ]; then echo \"NO-PURPOSE-NO-OWNED: $f\"; fi\ndone"},"output":"=== deep/research.md head (compiled stub?) ===\n---\ndescription: Autonomous deep-research loop: iterative investigation with convergence detection. Modes :auto, :confirm.\nargument-hint: \"<topic> [:auto|:confirm] [--spec-folder=PATH] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--convergence-mode=default|off|sliding-window|divergent] [--lineage-timeout-hours=N] [--stop-policy=convergence|max-iterations] [--no-resource-map] [--dry-run] [--executor=<type> [--model=X] [--config-dir=PATH] [--reasoning-effort=LEVEL] [--service-tier=TIER] [--executor-timeout=SECONDS] [--iters=N] [--count=N] [--label=X] ...] [--executors=<json>] [--concurrency=N] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, WebFetch, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context\n---\n\n# Deep Start Research Loop\n\nThin router for the deep-research loop. This command verifies the runtime agent, resolves setup and execution mode, loads the presentation contract, then executes the owned workflow YAML.\n\n## 1. ROUTER CONTRACT\n\nDo not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Agent dispatch, workflow steps, artifact-writing behavior, convergence detection, synthesis, and memory save behavior are owned by the workflow YAML assets.\n\nLoad the presentation contract before showing startup questions, dashboards, checkpoint text, success output, failure output, examples, or next-step prompts.\n\n> **Code Graph ownership:** `code_graph_query` and `code_graph_context` stay stable MCP tool IDs; implementation and docs now live under `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/`.\n\n> **EXECUTION PROTOCOL -- READ FIRST**\n>\n\n=== router-core markers: clean per-family count ===\n: total=3 owned_assets=0 presentation_boundary=0\n: total=3 owned_assets=0 presentation_boundary=0\n: total=3 owned_assets=0 presentation_boundary=0\n: total=3 owned_assets=0 presentation_boundary=0\n: total=3 owned_assets=0 presentation_boundary=0\n: total=3 owned_assets=0 presentation_boundary=0\n\n=== commands with NEITHER owned-assets NOR purpose/instructions (potential non-conformant) ===\nNO-PURPOSE-NO-OWNED: .opencode/commands/scripts/README.md\n","metadata":{"output":"=== deep/research.md head (compiled stub?) ===\n---\ndescription: Autonomous deep-research loop: iterative investigation with convergence detection. Modes :auto, :confirm.\nargument-hint: \"<topic> [:auto|:confirm] [--spec-folder=PATH] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--convergence-mode=default|off|sliding-window|divergent] [--lineage-timeout-hours=N] [--stop-policy=convergence|max-iterations] [--no-resource-map] [--dry-run] [--executor=<type> [--model=X] [--config-dir=PATH] [--reasoning-effort=LEVEL] [--service-tier=TIER] [--executor-timeout=SECONDS] [--iters=N] [--count=N] [--label=X] ...] [--executors=<json>] [--concurrency=N] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, WebFetch, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context\n---\n\n# Deep Start Research Loop\n\nThin router for the deep-research loop. This command verifies the runtime agent, resolves setup and execution mode, loads the presentation contract, then executes the owned workflow YAML.\n\n## 1. ROUTER CONTRACT\n\nDo not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Agent dispatch, workflow steps, artifact-writing behavior, convergence detection, synthesis, and memory save behavior are owned by the workflow YAML assets.\n\nLoad the presentation contract before showing startup questions, dashboards, checkpoint text, success output, failure output, examples, or next-step prompts.\n\n> **Code Graph ownership:** `code_graph_query` and `code_graph_context` stay stable MCP tool IDs; implementation and docs now live under `.opencode/skills/system-code-graph/`.\n\n> **EXECUTION PROTOCOL -- READ FIRST**\n>\n\n=== router-core markers: clean per-family count ===\n: total=3 owned_assets=0 presentation_boundary=0\n: total=3 owned_assets=0 presentation_boundary=0\n: total=3 owned_assets=0 presentation_boundary=0\n: total=3 owned_assets=0 presentation_boundary=0\n: total=3 owned_assets=0 presentation_boundary=0\n: total=3 owned_assets=0 presentation_boundary=0\n\n=== commands with NEITHER owned-assets NOR purpose/instructions (potential non-conformant) ===\nNO-PURPOSE-NO-OWNED: .opencode/commands/scripts/README.md\n","exit":0,"truncated":false},"title":"cd /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public\necho \"=== deep/research.md head (compiled stub?) ===\"\nhead -20 .opencode/commands/deep/research.md\necho \"\"\necho \"=== router-core markers: clean per-family count ===\"\nfor fam in create design speckit memory doctor deep; do\n  files=$(find .opencode/commands/$f -maxdepth 1 -name '*.md' 2>/dev/null)\n  total=$(echo \"$files\" | grep -c . )\n  core=$(echo \"$files\" | xargs rg -l '## .*OWNED ASSETS' 2>/dev/null | grep -c . )\n  pb=$(echo \"$files\" | xargs rg -l '## .*PRESENTATION BOUNDARY' 2>/dev/null | grep -c . )\n  echo \"$f: total=$total owned_assets=$core presentation_boundary=$pb\"\ndone\necho \"\"\necho \"=== commands with NEITHER owned-assets NOR purpose/instructions (potential non-conformant) ===\"\nfor f in $(find .opencode/commands -maxdepth 2 -name '*.md'); do\n  has_ow=$(rg -c 'OWNED ASSETS' \"$f\" 2>/dev/null || echo 0)\n  has_pur=$(rg -c '^## .*PURPOSE' \"$f\" 2>/dev/null || echo 0)\n  has_ins=$(rg -c '^## .*INSTRUCTIONS' \"$f\" 2>/dev/null || echo 0)\n  if [ \"$has_ow\" = \"0\" ] && [ \"$has_pur\" = \"0\" ]; then echo \"NO-PURPOSE-NO-OWNED: $f\"; fi\ndone","time":{"start":1784181166792,"end":1784181166912}},"id":"prt_f697c111e001OkcCZdqd45MJOk","sessionID":"ses_0968f2113ffehJfWsGHuGr12Oc","messageID":"msg_f697ba88c001q0kqIAFS4GmzFF"}}
