{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784181343679,"sessionID":"ses_0968f2113ffehJfWsGHuGr12Oc","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"call_8892518bd70745a0873c8c63","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md","newString":"<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n**Iteration 3 — RQ3 validator + benchmark coverage defects.** Enumerate the concrete command-surface defects that `validate_document.py --type command` and the 066 sk-doc-command deterministic adapter (S1–S5) fail to catch, then specify each as a deterministic, fixture-able check with a clean-control and a defect-control. Target the wholesale defect classes from RQ2: gate-obligation (router alternative), FQ MCP tools, argument-hint budget, presentation-leak/router-overclaim prose, topology classification, loader-gating consistency. Verify against the 000 contract's S1–S5 dimensions to avoid duplicating an existing check.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->","oldString":"<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n**Iteration 2 — RQ2 per-family conformance recurrence.** Sweep create/design/speckit/memory/doctor/deep to test whether the F1.1–F1.6 defect classes recur across families (→ canon gap, wholesale fix) or are isolated (→ one-off authoring error, per-file fix). Measure: missing-mandatory-gate prevalence, bare MCP tools, argument-hint length distribution, route-manifest topology presence, $ARGUMENTS echo usage. Output: a recurrence matrix mapping each defect class to the families it touches, with a wholesale-vs-per-file verdict per class.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -87,9 +87,9 @@\n ---\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n-**Iteration 2 — RQ2 per-family conformance recurrence.** Sweep create/design/speckit/memory/doctor/deep to test whether the F1.1–F1.6 defect classes recur across families (→ canon gap, wholesale fix) or are isolated (→ one-off authoring error, per-file fix). Measure: missing-mandatory-gate prevalence, bare MCP tools, argument-hint length distribution, route-manifest topology presence, $ARGUMENTS echo usage. Output: a recurrence matrix mapping each defect class to the families it touches, with a wholesale-vs-per-file verdict per class.\n+**Iteration 3 — RQ3 validator + benchmark coverage defects.** Enumerate the concrete command-surface defects that `validate_document.py --type command` and the 066 sk-doc-command deterministic adapter (S1–S5) fail to catch, then specify each as a deterministic, fixture-able check with a clean-control and a defect-control. Target the wholesale defect classes from RQ2: gate-obligation (router alternative), FQ MCP tools, argument-hint budget, presentation-leak/router-overclaim prose, topology classification, loader-gating consistency. Verify against the 000 contract's S1–S5 dimensions to avoid duplicating an existing check.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n \n ---\n \n","filediff":{"file":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -87,9 +87,9 @@\n ---\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n-**Iteration 2 — RQ2 per-family conformance recurrence.** Sweep create/design/speckit/memory/doctor/deep to test whether the F1.1–F1.6 defect classes recur across families (→ canon gap, wholesale fix) or are isolated (→ one-off authoring error, per-file fix). Measure: missing-mandatory-gate prevalence, bare MCP tools, argument-hint length distribution, route-manifest topology presence, $ARGUMENTS echo usage. Output: a recurrence matrix mapping each defect class to the families it touches, with a wholesale-vs-per-file verdict per class.\n+**Iteration 3 — RQ3 validator + benchmark coverage defects.** Enumerate the concrete command-surface defects that `validate_document.py --type command` and the 066 sk-doc-command deterministic adapter (S1–S5) fail to catch, then specify each as a deterministic, fixture-able check with a clean-control and a defect-control. Target the wholesale defect classes from RQ2: gate-obligation (router alternative), FQ MCP tools, argument-hint budget, presentation-leak/router-overclaim prose, topology classification, loader-gating consistency. Verify against the 000 contract's S1–S5 dimensions to avoid duplicating an existing check.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n \n ---\n \n","additions":1,"deletions":1},"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1784181343676,"end":1784181343677}},"id":"prt_f697ec5b8001ATUEb6phnu6p8i","sessionID":"ses_0968f2113ffehJfWsGHuGr12Oc","messageID":"msg_f697e598c001EHPZGg7SsoUGAR"}}
