{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784181539166,"sessionID":"ses_0968f2113ffehJfWsGHuGr12Oc","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"call_1655aa98eb88414a83b7c637","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md","newString":"<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n**Iteration 4 — RQ4 router/dispatch-logic improvements.** Argument-hint grammar, `$ARGUMENTS`/`$1..$N` handling, `:auto`/`:confirm` resolution completeness, and dual-runtime (opencode/codex/claude) parity. Audit how routers declare vs resolve modes, whether a `:auto`/`:confirm` hint always has matching MODE ROUTING + EXECUTION TARGETS, the raw `$ARGUMENTS` echo convention, and how the codex mirror stays in sync. Propose canon + check deltas per gap.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->","oldString":"<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n**Iteration 3 — RQ3 validator + benchmark coverage defects.** Enumerate the concrete command-surface defects that `validate_document.py --type command` and the 066 sk-doc-command deterministic adapter (S1–S5) fail to catch, then specify each as a deterministic, fixture-able check with a clean-control and a defect-control. Target the wholesale defect classes from RQ2: gate-obligation (router alternative), FQ MCP tools, argument-hint budget, presentation-leak/router-overclaim prose, topology classification, loader-gating consistency. Verify against the 000 contract's S1–S5 dimensions to avoid duplicating an existing check.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md\n==