{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784181559407,"sessionID":"ses_0968f2113ffehJfWsGHuGr12Oc","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_54fa03ee5b2e4f77ab89cfa0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"cd /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public\necho \"=== A. commands declaring :auto|:confirm in hint ===\"\nrg -l ':auto' .opencode/commands --glob '*.md' | grep -v assets | wc -l | tr -d ' '\necho \"=== B. do direct-dispatch families (memory) declare :auto/:confirm? memory hint lines ===\"\nrg -N '^argument-hint:' .opencode/commands/memory/*.md\necho \"=== C. raw '\\$ARGUMENTS' literal occurrences (echo usage) by family ===\"\nfor fam in create design speckit memory doctor deep; do\n  c=$(rg -c 'User request: \\$ARGUMENTS|^.*\\b\\$ARGUMENTS\\b' .opencode/commands/$f/*.md 2>/dev/null | wc -l | tr -d ' ')\n  echo \"$fam: $c files reference \\$ARGUMENTS\"\ndone\necho \"=== D. codex mirror existence ===\"\nls -d .codex/prompts 2>/dev/null && find .codex/prompts -name '*.md' 2>/dev/null | wc -l | tr -d ' ' || echo \"(no .codex/prompts)\"\necho \"=== E. sync-prompts.cjs role ===\"\nrg -n 'mirror|codex|claude|parity|prompt-sync' .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/codex/sync-prompts.cjs 2>/dev/null | head -8\necho \"=== F. \\$1..\\$N positional usage anywhere ===\"\nrg -n '\\$1|\\$2|\\bARGUMENTS\\b' .opencode/commands --glob '*.md' | grep -v assets | grep -E '\\$[0-9]' | head"},"output":"=== A. commands declaring :auto|:confirm in hint ===\n30\n=== B. do direct-dispatch families (memory) declare :auto/:confirm? memory hint lines ===\n.opencode/commands/memory/search.md:argument-hint: \"<query> [--intent <type>|--intent=<type>] | preflight <specFolder> <taskId> | postflight <specFolder> <taskId> | history <specFolder> | causal <memoryId> | link <sourceId> <targetId> <relation> | unlink <edgeId> | causal-stats | ablation | dashboard\"\n.opencode/commands/memory/save.md:argument-hint: \"<spec-folder>\"\n.opencode/commands/memory/learn.md:argument-hint: \"[rule-description] | list | edit <filename> | remove <filename> | budget\"\n.opencode/commands/memory/manage.md:argument-hint: \"[scan [--force]] | [cleanup] | [retention-sweep [--dry-run]] | [learned-expire [--dry-run]] | [learned-clear] | [ledger-sweep [--dry-run] [--apply]] | [bulk-delete <tier> [--older-than <days>] [--folder <spec>]] | [tier <id> <tier>] | [triggers <id>] | [validate <id> <true|false>] | [delete <id>] | [health] | [checkpoint <subcommand>] | [ingest <subcommand>]\"\n=== C. raw '$ARGUMENTS' literal occurrences (echo usage) by family ===\ncreate: 0 files reference $ARGUMENTS\ndesign: 0 files reference $ARGUMENTS\nspeckit: 0 files reference $ARGUMENTS\nmemory: 0 files reference $ARGUMENTS\ndoctor: 0 files reference $ARGUMENTS\ndeep: 0 files reference $ARGUMENTS\n=== D. codex mirror existence ===\n.codex/prompts\n38\n=== E. sync-prompts.cjs role ===\n12:const OUTPUT_DIR = path.join(REPO_ROOT, '.codex', 'prompts');\n121:    console.error('[codex-prompt-sync] Drift detected:');\n123:      console.error(`[codex-prompt-sync] ${item}`);\n128:  console.log(`[codex-prompt-sync] PASS: ${expectedOutputs.size} prompts are in sync.`);\n164:    `[codex-prompt-sync] Wrote ${changed} of ${expectedOutputs.size} generated prompts.`,\n183:  console.error(`[codex-prompt-sync] ERROR: ${error.message}`);\n=== F. $1..$N positional usage anywhere ===\n","metadata":{"output":"=== A. commands declaring :auto|:confirm in hint ===\n30\n=== B. do direct-dispatch families (memory) declare :auto/:confirm? memory hint lines ===\n.opencode/commands/memory/search.md:argument-hint: \"<query> [--intent <type>|--intent=<type>] | preflight <specFolder> <taskId> | postflight <specFolder> <taskId> | history <specFolder> | causal <memoryId> | link <sourceId> <targetId> <relation> | unlink <edgeId> | causal-stats | ablation | dashboard\"\n.opencode/commands/memory/save.md:argument-hint: \"<spec-folder>\"\n.opencode/commands/memory/learn.md:argument-hint: \"[rule-de