{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784181594708,"sessionID":"ses_0968f2113ffehJfWsGHuGr12Oc","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_a9060e72073b48e684899580","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"cd /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public\necho \"=== 'User request: \\$ARGUMENTS' exact files ===\"\nrg -ln 'User request: \\$ARGUMENTS' .opencode/commands --glob '*.md' | grep -v '/assets/'\necho \"\"\necho \"=== other \\$ARGUMENTS literal forms in router bodies (non-gate) ===\"\nrg -n '\\b\\$ARGUMENTS\\b' .opencode/commands/create/command.md .opencode/commands/doctor/update.md 2>/dev/null\necho \"\"\necho \"=== claude runtime mirror? ===\"\nls -d .claude/commands 2>/dev/null && find .claude/commands -name '*.md' 2>/dev/null | wc -l | tr -d ' ' || echo \"(no .claude/commands)\"\necho \"=== sync-prompts: does it target claude too? ===\"\nrg -n 'claude|\\.claude|runtime' .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/codex/sync-prompts.cjs | head\necho \"\"\necho \"=== memory/search.md: subaction dispatch — does it have MODE ROUTING or ARGUMENT ROUTING? ===\"\nrg -n '^## |subaction|ARGUMENT ROUTING|MODE ROUTING|EXECUTION TARGETS' .opencode/commands/memory/search.md | head -15"},"output":"=== 'User request: $ARGUMENTS' exact files ===\n.opencode/commands/create/manual-testing-playbook.md\n.opencode/commands/create/flowchart.md\n.opencode/commands/create/benchmark.md\n.opencode/commands/create/skill.md\n.opencode/commands/create/agent.md\n.opencode/commands/create/feature-catalog.md\n.opencode/commands/create/skill-parent.md\n.opencode/commands/create/changelog.md\n.opencode/commands/create/diff.md\n.opencode/commands/create/readme.md\n.opencode/commands/doctor/mcp.md\n.opencode/commands/create/command.md\n.opencode/commands/doctor/update.md\n.opencode/commands/doctor/speckit.md\n\n=== other $ARGUMENTS literal forms in router bodies (non-gate) ===\n\n=== claude runtime mirror? ===\n.claude/commands\n0\n=== sync-prompts: does it target claude too? ===\n75:    `This is the Codex runtime entry point for the \\`/${flatName}\\` command. The canonical, authoritative command definition lives in the OpenCode tree at:`,\n\n=== memory/search.md: subaction dispatch — does it have MODE ROUTING or ARGUMENT ROUTING? ===\n11:## 1. ROUTER CONTRACT\n21:- **When `ARGS_PRESENT=true`: you MUST execute retrieval (or the analysis route) on `QUERY` now.** Do NOT ask the startup question, and do NOT treat a populated `QUERY` as empty. Go to the retrieval route in §4 EXECUTION TARGETS, or the analysis route in §4 EXECUTION TARGETS when the first token of `QUERY` is a known analysis subcommand.\n22:- **ONLY IF `ARGS_PRESENT=false`:** follow startup routing in §3 MODE ROUTING and ask the one open-ended question.\n32:## 2. OWNED ASSETS\n42:## 3. MODE ROUTING\n48:3. **If `ARGS_PRESENT=true`:** route `QUERY` to the retrieval route (§4 EXECUTION TARGETS), or to the analysis route (§4 EXECUTION TARGETS) when the first token of `QUERY` is a known analysis subcommand. Execute now — do NOT ask the startup question.\n50:5. Render the response from the presentation contract; retrieval results must use the inline contract in §4 EXECUTION TARGETS.\n52:Startup routing. **Reach this ONLY IF `ARGS_PRESENT=false`.** A populated `QUERY` never reaches here — if `ARGS_PRESENT=true`, you already executed the retrieval or analysis route in §4 EXECUTION TARGETS. When `ARGS_PRESENT=false`, ask one open-ended question from the presentation asset. Do not dump the full intent/menu list at startup. Treat a custom answer as the retrieval query.\n54:## 4. EXECUTION TARGETS\n137:## 5. PRESENTATION BOUNDARY\n148:## 6. WORKFLOW SUMMARY\n","metadata":{"output":"=== 'User request: $ARGUMENTS' exact files ===\n.opencode/commands/create/manual-testing-playbook.md\n.opencode/commands/create/flowchart.md\n.opencode/commands/create/benchmark.md\n.opencode/commands/create/skill.md\n.opencode/commands/create/agent.md\n.opencode/commands/create/feature-catalog.md\n.opencode/commands/create/skill-parent.md\n.opencode/commands/create/changelog.md\n.opencode/commands/create/diff.md\n.opencode/commands/create/readme.md\n.opencode/commands/doctor/mcp.md\n.opencode/commands/create/command.md\n.opencode/commands/doctor/update.md\n.opencode/commands/doctor/speckit.md\n\n=== other $ARGUMENTS literal forms in router bodies (non-gate) ===\n\n=== claude runtime mirror? ===\n.claude/commands\n0\n=== sync-prompts: does it target claude too? ===\n75:    `This is the Codex runtime entry point for the \\`/${flatName}\\` command. The canonical, authoritative command definition lives in the OpenCode tree at:`,\n\n=== memory/search.md: subaction dispatch — does it have MODE ROUTING or ARGUMENT ROUTING? ===\n11:## 1. ROUTER CONTRACT\n21:- **When `ARGS_PRESENT=true`: you MUST execute retrieval (or the analysis route) on `QUERY` now.** Do NOT ask the startup question, and do NOT treat a populated `QUERY` as empty. Go to the retrieval route in §4 EXECUTION TARGETS, or the analysis route in §4 EXECUTION TARGETS when the first token of `QUERY` is a known analysis subcommand.\n22:- **ONLY IF `ARGS_PRESENT=false`:** follow startup routing in §3 MODE ROUTING and ask the one open-ended question.\n32:## 2. OWNED ASSETS\n42:## 3. MODE ROUTING\n48:3. **If `ARGS_PRESENT=true`:** route `QUERY` to the retrieval route (§4 EXECUTION TARGETS), or to the analysis route (§4 EXECUTION TARGETS) when the first token of `QUERY` is a known analysis subcommand. Execute now — do NOT ask the startup question.\n50:5. Render the response from the presentation contract; retrieval results must use the inline contract in §4 EXECUTION TARGETS.\n52:Startup routing. **Reach this ONLY IF `ARGS_PRESENT=false`.** A populated `QUERY` never reaches here — if `ARGS_PRESENT=true`, you already executed the retrieval or analysis route in §4 EXECUTION TARGETS. When `ARGS_PRESENT=false`, ask one open-ended question from the presentation asset. Do not dump the full intent/menu list at startup. Treat a custom answer as the retrieval query.\n54:## 4. EXECUTION TARGETS\n137:## 5. PRESENTATION BOUNDARY\n148:## 6. WORKFLOW SUMMARY\n","exit":0,"truncated":false},"title":"cd /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public\necho \"=== 'User request: \\$ARGUMENTS' exact files ===\"\nrg -ln 'User request: \\$ARGUMENTS' .opencode/commands --glob '*.md' | grep -v '/assets/'\necho \"\"\necho \"=== other \\$ARGUMENTS literal forms in router bodies (non-gate) ===\"\nrg -n '\\b\\$ARGUMENTS\\b' .opencode/commands/create/command.md .opencode/commands/doctor/update.md 2>/dev/null\necho \"\"\necho \"=== claude runtime mirror? ===\"\nls -d .claude/commands 2>/dev/null && find .claude/commands -name '*.md' 2>/dev/null | wc -l | tr -d ' ' || echo \"(no .claude/commands)\"\necho \"=== sync-prompts: does it target claude too? ===\"\nrg -n 'claude|\\.claude|runtime' .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/codex/sync-prompts.cjs | head\necho \"\"\necho \"=== memory/search.md: subaction dispatch — does it have MODE ROUTING or ARGUMENT ROUTING? ===\"\nrg -n '^## |subaction|ARGUMENT ROUTING|MODE ROUTING|EXECUTION TARGETS' .opencode/commands/memory/search.md | head -15","time":{"start":1784181594701,"end":1784181594702}},"id":"prt_f69829a2c001PYRd78rQBUQ43b","sessionID":"ses_0968f2113ffehJfWsGHuGr12Oc","messageID":"msg_f698217f7001n6jdfBu46LI68i"}}
