{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784181735901,"sessionID":"ses_0968f2113ffehJfWsGHuGr12Oc","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"edit","callID":"call_f46a29451df6460980488c33","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md","newString":"<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n**Iteration 5 — RQ5 authoring ergonomics + cross-RQ prioritization.** Consolidate the recurring authoring failures (fat monolith hints, missing loader-gating frontmatter, prose drift between a command and its presentation/guides) into template/logic changes. Then cross-cut all C1.x–C4.x candidate deltas into a single prioritized backlog (P0/P1/P2) with dependency ordering (C3.6 enabler first), ready to seed follow-on remediation packets. Final pre-synthesis broadening pass.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->","oldString":"<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n**Iteration 4 — RQ4 router/dispatch-logic improvements.** Argument-hint grammar, `$ARGUMENTS`/`$1..$N` handling, `:auto`/`:confirm` resolution completeness, and dual-runtime (opencode/codex/claude) parity — where the canon is silent and the corpus has drift (raw `$ARGUMENTS` echo, undeclared mode targets).\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->"},"output":"Edit applied successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"diff":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -87,9 +87,9 @@\n ---\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n-**Iteration 4 — RQ4 router/dispatch-logic improvements.** Argument-hint grammar, `$ARGUMENTS`/`$1..$N` handling, `:auto`/`:confirm` resolution completeness, and dual-runtime (opencode/codex/claude) parity. Audit how routers declare vs resolve modes, whether a `:auto`/`:confirm` hint always has matching MODE ROUTING + EXECUTION TARGETS, the raw `$ARGUMENTS` echo convention, and how the codex mirror stays in sync. Propose canon + check deltas per gap.\n+**Iteration 5 — RQ5 authoring ergonomics + cross-RQ prioritization.** Consolidate the recurring authoring failures (fat monolith hints, missing loader-gating frontmatter, prose drift between a command and its presentation/guides) into template/logic changes. Then cross-cut all C1.x–C4.x candidate deltas into a single prioritized backlog (P0/P1/P2) with dependency ordering (C3.6 enabler first), ready to seed follow-on remediation packets. Final pre-synthesis broadening pass.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n \n ---\n \n","filediff":{"file":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -87,9 +87,9 @@\n ---\n \n <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n-**Iteration 4 — RQ4 router/dispatch-logic improvements.** Argument-hint grammar, `$ARGUMENTS`/`$1..$N` handling, `:auto`/`:confirm` resolution completeness, and dual-runtime (opencode/codex/claude) parity. Audit how routers declare vs resolve modes, whether a `:auto`/`:confirm` hint always has matching MODE ROUTING + EXECUTION TARGETS, the raw `$ARGUMENTS` echo convention, and how the codex mirror stays in sync. Propose canon + check deltas per gap.\n+**Iteration 5 — RQ5 authoring ergonomics + cross-RQ prioritization.** Consolidate the recurring authoring failures (fat monolith hints, missing loader-gating frontmatter, prose drift between a command and its presentation/guides) into template/logic changes. Then cross-cut all C1.x–C4.x candidate deltas into a single prioritized backlog (P0/P1/P2) with dependency ordering (C3.6 enabler first), ready to seed follow-on remediation packets. Final pre-synthesis broadening pass.\n <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n \n ---\n \n","additions":1,"deletions":1},"truncated":false},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/066-command-surface-benchmark/012-command-improvement-research/research/lineages/glm52-max/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1784181735898,"end":1784181735900}},"id":"prt_f6984c1d4001RZQwLDTvxmLz03","sessionID":"ses_0968f2113ffehJfWsGHuGr12Oc","messageID":"msg_f69848c6d001itMsBu7stAn0Ah"}}
